A rubbing of this mirror, presumed to be the one from this kofun, is stored at the **Nara Prefectural Tenri Library**{{Citation needed|date=February 2020}}, and a replica is preserved at the **Anthropology Museum of Nanzan University**.
The mirror is now attributed to an excavation in **Tsuchida, {{ill|Kani, Gifu|ja|可児市|12=draft|12=draft}}, Gifu Prefecture**, and is **from the same mold as mirrors discovered at**: - **{{ill|Saikumezuka Kofun|ja|西求女塚古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}** (Hyōgo Prefecture) - **{{ill|Tsubai Ōtsukayama Kofun|ja|椿井大塚山古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}** (Kyoto Prefecture) - **{{ill|Shiroyama No.1 Kofun (Katori, Chiba)|ja|城山1号墳 (香取市)|12=draft|12=draft}}** (Chiba Prefecture)
